What are CloudWatch Alarmsâ€™ actions and how can you use them to respond to events?
Answer: CloudWatch Alarm actions are the responses triggered when an alarm state is reached.
Actions can include sending notifications (e.g., via SNS), executing an Auto Scaling policy, or invoking a Lambda
function. These actions allow you to automate responses to events based on alarm conditions.
